<h1>Transliteration</h1>

<p>Old Persian is indicated by the language shift <code>%peo</code>;
following this language shift, the ATF processor reads Old Persian 
transliterated as a sequence of graphemes joined by hyphens as with
other graphemic input.</p>

<p>To write in transcription, use the convention for 'normalized'
input, as in Akkadian: i.e., follow the language shift with
<code>/n</code>.</p>

